# UI/UX Guidelines & Design System (T1-WSP-Embedded)

> **Philosophy:** "Tactics, not Talent."  
> We prioritize **Stability**, **Readability**, and the **Rule of Least Power**. Our tools should feel "clean, linear, and professional"—high fidelity through strict adherence to fundamentals, not flashy custom CSS.

---

## 1. Core Design Principles (WSP Identity)

### A. The "WSP" Aesthetic (Premium & Linear)
- **Black & White Foundation:** The UI should be predominantly Black (Navigation, Primary Actions) and White (Content, Cards).
- **Red Accents:** Use WSP Red (#ff372f, see packages/brand-wsp/colors.json) sparingly for active states, highlights, or critical alerts. Never use it for large backgrounds.
- **Data Density:** Enterprise tools need to be dense but legible. Use 13px-14px styling.

> Note: All application colours (React, Python, etc.) MUST be sourced from the centralised palette: packages/brand-wsp/colors.json.

## 2. Technical Implementation (Tailwind CSS)

### A. Layouts & Navigation
Requirement: Navigation bars must be Black with White text.

The "Shell" Pattern:
// Common layout for all internal tools
<div className="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 flex flex-col">
  {/* WSP Global Header */}
  <header className="bg-black text-white h-16 flex items-center px-6 shadow-md">
    <div className="font-bold text-xl tracking-tight">WSP <span className="text-[#ff372f]">Collisions</span></div>
    {/* Navigation Links: White text, subtle hover */}
    <nav className="ml-auto space-x-6 text-sm font-medium">
      <a href="#" className="hover:text-gray-300 transition-colors">Dashboard</a>
      <a href="#" className="hover:text-gray-300 transition-colors">Settings</a>
    </nav>
  </header>
  <main className="flex-1 p-8 max-w-7xl w-full mx-auto">
    {/* Content */}
  </main>
</div>

### B. Cards & Containers
- Preferred: bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-none (Sharp corners feel more "Engineering/Technical").
- Shadows: detailed but subtle. shadow-sm.

### C. Typography
- Primary Corporate Font: PP Neue Montreal
- Fallback Font: Arial
- Headings (Medium): Use uppercase for impact headings (5 words or less). font-sans font-medium text-black.
- Subheads (Bold): Highlight key text with sentence case. font-sans font-bold text-black.
- Body (Regular): Sentence case for all general text. font-sans font-normal text-gray-700.

### D. Actions & Buttons
- Primary: bg-black text-white hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors (Standard WSP Primary).
- Secondary: bg-white border border-gray-300 text-black hover:bg-gray-50.
- Accent/Alert: bg-[#ff372f] text-white hover:bg-red-700.

### E. Assets & Logos
All official WSP logos are stored in packages/brand-wsp/assets.
- WSP Red Logo: packages/brand-wsp/assets/WSP Red Logo.png (Primary use on White backgrounds)
- WSP White Logo: packages/brand-wsp/assets/WSP White Logo.png (Use on Black/Dark backgrounds)
- WSP Black Logo: packages/brand-wsp/assets/WSP Black Logo.png (Use only for monochrome print/reports)

Usage Rule:
- Navigation Bar: Always use the White Logo or White Text.
- Reports/Docs: Use the Red Logo on white paper.

---

## 3. Component Standards (The "Rule of Least Power")

### A. Data Tables
- Headers: text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider bg-gray-50
- Rows: border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors
- Alignment: Numbers right-aligned, Text left-aligned.

### B. Forms
- Labels: block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1
- Inputs: block w-full rounded-md border-gray-300 focus:border-blue-500 focus:ring-blue-500 sm:text-sm
- Validation: Inline error messages in text-red-600 text-sm.

## 4. Accessibility (A11y)
- Focus Rings: Never remove outline-none without replacing it with a custom ring.
- Semantic HTML: Use <button>, not <div onClick>.

## 5. "Agent X" Review Checklist
Verify before completion:
- [ ] Roughly aligned elements use the same spacing scale (e.g., gap-4).
- [ ] No arbitrary pixel values (e.g., width: 357px).
- [ ] Primary action is distinct from secondary actions.
- [ ] Empty states are handled.
- [ ] No horizontal scrolling on standard 1080p monitors.

